form.preferredDefinition: From the Global Surveillance Network of the International Society of Travel Medicine (ISTM) and the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), The GeoSentinel protocol is a self-reported questionnaire that collects information on a respondent's recent (within the last 6 months) and previous (within the last 5 years) travel history. It also provides a template for the clinician to use in assessing the exposure details.

form.preferredDefinition: This protocol is a self- or proxy-administered questionnaire from the American Health Information Management Association (AHIMA) that collects information on whether a respondent has a specific medical issue and if so, the date of onset.

form.longName: PhenX PX161401 - Personal And Family History Of Autoimmune And Inflammato
form.preferredDefinition: This protocol includes self-administered questions from the Lupus Family Registry and Repository (LFRR). Respondents answer questions regarding their personal history and family history of various autoimmune and inflammatory disorders.

question.questionText: Prominent rash on cheeks for more than 1 month (prominent_rash_on_cheeks)
Skin breaks out in the sun (not sunburn) (skin_breaksout_in_sun)
Sores in mouth for more than 2 weeks (mouth_sores)
Arthritis or rheumatism for more than 3 months (arthritis_more_than_3_months)
Pain for more than a few days when taking deep breath (pleurisy) (pleurisy)
Low blood counts (anemia, low white blood cell count, or low platelet count) (low_blood_counts)
If yes or still present Anemia (lbc_anemia)
If yes or still present Hemolytic anemia (lbc_hemolytic_anemia)
If yes or still present Low white blood cell count (low_white_blood_cell_count)
If yes or still present Low platelet count (low_platelet_count)
Positive skin test for tuberculosis (tuberculin, PPD, or TINE test) (positive_tuberculosis_skin_test)
Positive blood test for syphilis (VDRL or RPR) (positive_syphilis_blood_test)
Mental illness (requiring hospital admission) or psychosis or hallucinations (mental_illness)
Rapid hair loss NOT due to chemotherapy (rapid_hair_loss)
If yes or still present, age you first had mono (age_first_had_mononucleosis)
Slow heart beat (less than 50 beats per minute) (slow_heart_beat)
Graying of all or nearly all hair before 35 (graying_hair_before_35)
